Network management commands
***********************************
1.check the ip address

  command :1. ip addr
           2. ip a

2.check the gateway
>check the default gateway and network routing

  command : ip route

3.check the gateway connectivity
  command : ping -c 4 route-ip

  example : ping -c 4 192.168.106.2 

>it shows like :64 bytes from 192.168.106.2: icmp_seq=1 ttl=128 time=0.193 ms
           4 packets transmitted, 4 received, 0% packet loss  
  Here the packet is small pieace of data sents over a network
  each packet has three phases
   a.Header : Header is works source ip and destination like (8.8.8.8)
   b.Data: Data is gives the actual data
   c.Footer:Footer is for error checking

4.check the test internet connectivity
>check the system can reach the internet without DNS

  command : ping -c 3 8.8.8.8

5.check the DNS 
check the DNS working 
  
  command : ping -c 3 google.com

6.check the DNS config file
  command : cat /etc/resolv.conf
  shows the which dns server runs our system

>if the DNS is not working check by using this commands

>if nslookup command is not found then "yum install bind-utils -y"

  command : nslookup google.com (Debug the DNS issue and ping works domain is not working)
            host google.com
            dig google.com (Advanced DNS tool like:detailed info like TTL, query time)

>check the DNS without internet 

  command :ping 8.8.8.8

>DNS is not working
  a.check the internet 
     ping 8.8.8.8
  b.check the DNS
     nslookup google.com
  c.check the DNS server 
     cat /etc/resolv.conf
  d.fix DNS server
     echo "nameserver 8.8.8.8" > /etc/resolv.conf 

7.check the open ports
>using which services are running and which ports are open

  command : ss -tulnp
>only show ssh details 
  command : ss -tulnp | grep 22
  
8.Check the firewall settings for the active zone
  command :firewall-cmd --list-all

9.Check the hostname 
  
  command : hostname

10.Quick ip check
  command : hostname -I
  this command shows all ip address in our system

11.Check interface stastics
  command :ip -s link
  shows the network interface stastics

12.Check the MAC address
  command : ip neigh
  shows ARP table(table which maps ip address and MAC address for local network communication )
  check the communication gateway  
  verify network devices
  troubleshooting connectivity

13.check the path and destination
  command : traceroute 8.8.8.8
  shows the path (hops) between your system and destination

  if command is not found then install 'yum install traceroute -y'

14.Check the active connections,listening ports,and ports
  command : netstat -tulnp
  
15.Check the network interface status
  command : nmcli device status

  check if network is active and identify the issues early

16.Check the connection details
  command : nmcli connection show
  
  show all saved connection profiles

17.shows the complete network configuration of connection 
  command : nmcli connection show ens160

